<GuideLayout
  title="About Us — Research Standards & Author Credentials"
  description="How we verify visa rules, rent data and school fees using official GCC government sources. Author Mottalib Radif MBA INSEAD. Quarterly review cycle since 2024."
  canonical="/about/"
  schemas={schemas}
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: "Home", url: "/" }, { name: "About", url: "/about/" }]}
>
  <h1>About Arabia Expat 2026</h1>

  <p>Arabia Expat is the definitive online resource for professionals relocating to the United Arab Emirates, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia. We provide free, accurate, and up-to-date information on visa processes, housing, schools, utilities, driving licences, healthcare, and daily life across the Gulf region. For salary data and employment-specific resources, visit our sister site <a href="https://taxfreesalaries.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">taxfreesalaries.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>Our Mission</h2>
  <p>We believe that every professional considering a Gulf career deserves access to transparent, reliable information. Our mission is to help expats with the guides and resources they need to make informed decisions about relocating, settling in, and building a life in the Gulf. Whether you are comparing salary offers between Dubai and Riyadh, evaluating school options for your children, understanding visa requirements, or estimating your monthly budget in Doha, Arabia Expat provides the practical, data-driven guidance you need.</p>

  <h2>About the Author</h2>
  <h3>Mottalib Radif, MBA INSEAD</h3>
  <p>Mottalib Radif holds an MBA from INSEAD, one of the world's leading business schools, and has spent over a decade advising professionals on Gulf region career transitions. His research covers labor law, compensation structures, immigration policy, and cost-of-living analysis across the UAE, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia.</p>
  <p>With firsthand experience navigating the Gulf employment market, Mottalib combines academic rigor with practical insights to create resources that genuinely help expats. His work has been cited by career consultancies, immigration advisors, and financial planners serving the Gulf expatriate community. His focus areas include salary benchmarking, visa and residency policy analysis, and comparative guides that help professionals choose the right Gulf destination for their career stage and family situation.</p>

  <h2>Our Methodology</h2>
  <p>We take accuracy seriously. Our data collection and verification process includes the following steps:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Official government sources:</strong> All legal information, tax rates, and regulatory details are sourced from official government publications, including the UAE Ministry of Human Resources and Emiratisation (MoHRE), Saudi Ministry of Human Resources and Social Development (MHRSD), and Qatar Ministry of Administrative Development, Labour and Social Affairs (MADLSA).</li>
    <li><strong>Salary data verification:</strong> Our salary ranges are compiled from job posting analysis across major platforms (LinkedIn, Bayt.com, GulfTalent), recruitment agency surveys, and industry reports. We cross-reference multiple sources and update data quarterly.</li>
    <li><strong>Calculator accuracy:</strong> All financial calculators are built using the exact formulas specified in the relevant country's labor law. We test calculations against known scenarios and official examples published by government entities.</li>
    <li><strong>Regular updates:</strong> Labor laws, visa regulations, and economic conditions change. We review and update all content at least quarterly to ensure accuracy.</li>
    <li><strong>Peer review:</strong> Key content, particularly legal and financial information, is reviewed by professionals with relevant expertise in Gulf employment law and finance.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
  <p>Arabia Expat maintains complete editorial independence. Our content is not sponsored by recruitment agencies, employers, or government entities. We provide objective information to help professionals make their own informed decisions. Where we reference specific companies or services, it is for informational purposes only and does not constitute an endorsement.</p>

  <h2>What We Cover</h2>
  <p>Arabia Expat covers the full spectrum of expatriate life in the Gulf region. Our content spans the following areas:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Country and city guides:</strong> Comprehensive overviews of life in the UAE, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia, including city-specific guides for Dubai, Abu Dhabi, Doha, Riyadh, Jeddah, and the Dammam-Khobar-Dhahran metropolitan area.</li>
    <li><strong>Cost of living:</strong> Detailed breakdowns of housing, groceries, transport, utilities, healthcare, and education costs with specific prices in local currencies and euro equivalents.</li>
    <li><strong>Visa and residency:</strong> Up-to-date information on work visas, dependent visas, Golden Visas, Premium Residency programs, and the documentation required for each country.</li>
    <li><strong>Practical setup guides:</strong> Step-by-step instructions for utilities registration, driving licence conversion, mobile phone setup, banking, and other essential tasks when relocating.</li>
    <li><strong>Country comparisons:</strong> Data-driven comparisons between Gulf countries and cities, covering salaries, VAT rates, housing costs, gratuity rules, and lifestyle factors.</li>
    <li><strong>Relocating-from guides:</strong> Country-specific advice for professionals moving from India, Pakistan, the Philippines, Egypt, Bangladesh, the UK, the US, and France.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Differ From Other Resources</h2>
  <p>Unlike generic expat forums or government tourism websites, Arabia Expat focuses exclusively on the practical, financial, and logistical aspects of Gulf relocation. We provide specific numbers and data points rather than vague generalizations. When we say rent in Dubai Marina costs AED 7,000-10,000 per month, that figure is based on current market analysis, not a rough estimate from years ago. We update pricing data quarterly and cite official government sources for all regulatory information. Our comparison tools allow side-by-side evaluation of different countries and cities, making it easier to assess where your salary and lifestyle preferences align best.</p>

  <h2>Accuracy Disclaimer</h2>
  <p>While we strive for accuracy, the information on Arabia Expat is provided for general guidance and educational purposes. It should not be considered as legal, financial, or immigration advice. Laws, regulations, and market conditions change, and individual circumstances vary. Government policies regarding visas, residency, and employment can be updated with limited notice. We recommend consulting with qualified professionals (lawyers, accountants, immigration consultants) for advice specific to your situation. All prices and salary figures represent ranges based on market research and may vary by location, timing, and individual circumstances. Please review our <a href="/terms/">Terms of Use</a> for complete disclaimers.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>We welcome corrections, suggestions, and feedback. If you notice any inaccuracies, have updated information that could improve our content, or would like to suggest topics for future coverage, reach out at <a href="mailto:contact@arabiaexpat.com">contact@arabiaexpat.com</a>. Maintaining accuracy is our top priority, and we take reader corrections seriously. We aim to respond to all substantive feedback within 5 business days and incorporate verified corrections into our content promptly.</p>

